description: Using a high-end mass spectrometry, we screened phosphoproteins and phosphopeptides in five types of Alzheimer's disease (AD) mouse models (5xFAD, APP-tg, PS1-tg, PS2-tg and  APP-KI) and four types of frontotemporal lobar degeneration (FTLD) mouse models(CHMP2B-KI, PGRN-KI, VCP-KI and TDP43-KI) at multiple time points (1, 3 and 6 months).
